    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every Google Ads click you pay for is supposed to turn into a phone call. But when that call goes to voicemail, <strong>72% of homeowners hang up</strong> without leaving a message — and you just paid $25–$600 for nothing. This is the hidden cost of missed calls in home-service advertising.</p>

      <p>Most tradies obsess over keywords, bids, and ad copy but ignore what happens <em>after</em> the phone rings. That gap is where the real money leaks out. Here is exactly how missed calls eat your ad budget — and how to stop it.</p>

      <h2>The Math Behind a Missed Call</h2>
      <p>Let's put real numbers on it. A typical HVAC contractor in a mid-size market spends $50–$150 per day on Google Ads. Each qualified call costs $25–$60 in ad spend. When that call rings your office phone and nobody answers:</p>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Ad Spend Lost</th><th>Revenue Lost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1 missed call/day</td><td>$25–$60/day</td><td>$200–$600/job</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5 missed calls/day</td><td>$125–$300/day</td><td>$1,000–$3,000/day</td></tr>
          <tr><td>30 missed calls/month</td><td>$750–$1,800/month</td><td>$6,000–$18,000/month</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p>The ad spend itself is bad enough. But the real hit is <strong>lost lifetime customer value</strong>. That homeowner who hung up on your voicemail called your competitor next — and they answered. You lost not just one job, but every future job that homeowner would have booked.</p>

      <h2>Why 72% of Homeowners Hang Up on Voicemail</h2>
      <p>This statistic comes from call behavior research across home-service industries. When a homeowner needs a plumber at midnight, a roofer after a storm, or an electrician on Sunday morning, they are in <strong>scarcity mode</strong>. They call the first result they see. They expect an answer. Voicemail signals: "We're not available."</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Urgency drives hang-ups:</strong> The more urgent the need (burst pipe, no heat, storm damage), the less likely the caller leaves a message</li>
        <li><strong>Competition is one click away:</strong> Your ad is one of many. The homeowner simply scrolls back up and calls the next ad</li>
        <li><strong>Voicemail feels like rejection:</strong> Homeowners interpret a missed call as "too busy to take new work" and move on</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Missed Calls Inflate Your CPA</h2>
      <p>Google Ads runs on a conversion-based auction model. If your ads generate calls that don't convert (because nobody answers), Google's algorithm notices. It interprets "call not answered" as a low-quality lead source and <strong>raises your cost-per-click</strong> over time. The math is brutal:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>10 calls generated by Google Ads → 7 go to voicemail (72% hang-up rate) → only 3 converted</li>
        <li>Your effective CPA was supposed to be $40. Your actual CPA: <strong>$133</strong></li>
        <li>Google sees low conversion volume → bids increase → same thing next month</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This is the hidden feedback loop that quietly doubles ad costs for tradies who don't answer their phones. The fix isn't a better keyword list. It's answering every call.</p>

      <h2>What 24/7 Call Coverage Looks Like for Tradies</h2>
      <p>The solution is a <strong>call answering and qualification system</strong> that picks up before the third ring, every single time. Not a virtual receptionist who transfers leads during business hours. Not an answering service that takes a message. A system that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Answers 24/7/365</strong> — nights, weekends, holidays, storm surges</li>
        <li><strong>Verifies the caller</strong> — confirms homeowner status, postal code, and work type</li>
        <li><strong>Books the appointment</strong> — directly into your calendar with all details captured</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This turns every ad click into a confirmed appointment. Your CPA drops back to what you planned for — and your Google Ads account gets a steady stream of conversion signals that <em>lower</em> your future ad costs.</p>

