      <h2>Why Most Tradies Don't Realize This Is Happening</h2>
      <p>The problem is <strong>invisible without call tracking</strong>. Most tradies run Google Ads alongside their Google Business Profile and don't know which calls came from which source. They see some calls come through, book some jobs, and assume the ad account is working. But 70%+ of their ad-generated calls are going to voicemail — they just don't have the data to see it.</p>
      <p>Adding call tracking to your Google Ads account reveals the truth immediately. Once you see that half your calls go unanswered, the business case for 24/7 call answering becomes obvious.</p>

      <h2>What Changes When You Capture Every Call</h2>
      <p>Tradies who implement call recovery systems see measurable shifts within the first 30 days:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Appointment volume increases 40–60%</strong> — because calls that previously went to voicemail now become booked jobs</li>
        <li><strong>Ad cost per lead drops significantly</strong> — Google's algorithm sees more conversions and reduces your CPC</li>
        <li><strong>Off-hours revenue appears</strong> — nights and weekends generate appointments you were previously missing entirely</li>
        <li><strong>Morning scheduling chaos disappears</strong> — appointments are already in your calendar when you start the day</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Is Call Recovery Right for Your Trade?</h2>
      <p>If you run Google Ads and any of these describe your business, call recovery is essential:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You get calls after hours or on weekends</li>
        <li>You've ever missed a call while on another job</li>
        <li>You have a voicemail inbox full of hang-ups</li>
        <li>Your Google Ads CPA has been creeping up month over month</li>
        <li>You're not sure which leads come from ads vs. your Google Business Profile</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Every trade — <a href="/blog/google-ads-for-plumbers/">plumbers</a>, electricians, HVAC, roofers, landscapers, painters — faces the same leak in the bucket. The solution is the same: answer every call, capture every lead, book every appointment.</p>

      <p>Google Ads works when you let it. The missing piece isn't more budget or better keywords — it's making sure someone actually picks up the phone.</p>
